title: Alistipes putredinis DSM 17216
paragraph: Alistipes putredinis (GenBank Accession Number for 16S rDNA gene: L16497) is a member of the Bacteroidetes division of the domain bacteria and has been isolated from human feces. It has been found in 16S rDNA sequence-based enumerations of the colonic microbiota of adult humans (Eckburg et. al. (2005), Ley et. al. (2006)).|||Keywords: GSC:MIxS;MIGS:5.0
